<title>Algebraic Geometry / Commutative Algebra</title>
</head>


<font size=+2> Reading seminar in algebraic geometry.</font><br>
<font size=+2> Spring 2019. The minimal model program.</font>

<br>
<br>

<p>
This semester the reading seminar will study the minimal model program
</p>
<p>
The seminar will consist of talks by faculty followed by talks by graduate students. We will attempt to make the seminar accessible to everyone.
</p>
<p>
The seminar will meet on Friday afternoons, 2:30PM--3:30PM, in LGRT 1334. 
</p>
<br><hr><br>

<b>Tentative Schedule</b>
<br>
<br>
1/25 Organizational meeting.
<br>
<br>
2/1 No meeting
<br>
<br>
2/8. Jenia Tevelev. Introduction to MMP. <a href="http://www.math.umass.edu/calendar/reading-seminar-in-algebraic-geometry/18891">Abstract</a>.
<a href="lecture_notes_2_8.pdf">Lecture notes</a>.
<br>
<br>
2/15. Paul Hacking. Introduction to MMP. II.
<br>
<br>
2/22. Luca Schaffler. Introduction to toric varieties.
<br>
<br>
3/1. David Cox. The minimal model program for toric varieties.
<br>
<br>
3/8. Kuan-Wen Lai. The Sarkisov program.
<br>
<br>
3/15. No meeting (Spring Break)
<br>
<br>
3/22. No meeting (AGNES)
<br>
<br>
3/29. Sebastian Torres. Mori dream spaces. <a href="http://www.math.umass.edu/calendar/reading-seminar-in-algebraic-geometry/19015">Abstract</a>.
<br>
<br>
4/5. Arie Stern. Singularities of the minimal model program.
<br>
<br>
4/12. No meeting (Ellis memorial conference)
<br>
<br>
4/19. Jennifer Li. The cone theorem for smooth projective varieties. < a href="https://www.math.umass.edu/calendar/reading-seminar-in-algebraic-geometry/19029">Abstract</a>.
<br>
<br>
4/26. Angelica Simonetti.
<br>
