<b>References</b>
<br>
<br>
J. Koll&aacute;r, The structure of algebraic threefolds: an introduction to Mori's program. <a href=" http://www.ams.org/journals/bull/1987-17-02/S0273-0979-1987-15548-0/home.html">journal</a>.
<br>
<br>
J. Koll&aacute;r and S. Mori, Birational geometry of algebraic varieties. <a href="https://books.google.com/books?id=YrysxvPbBLwC&source=gbs_navlinks_s">googlebooks</a>.
<br>
<br>
J. Koll&aacute;r, Exercises in the birational geometry of algebraic varieties. <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/0809.2579">arXiv</a>.
<br>
<br>
S. Mori, Threefolds whose canonical bundles are not numerically effective. <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2007050">JSTOR</a>.
<br>
<br>
M. Reid, Chapters on algebraic surfaces, Chapter D. <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/alg-geom/9602006">arXiv</a>.
<br>
<br>
D. Cox, J. Little, and H. Schenck, Toric varieties. <a href="https://books.google.com/books?id=AoSDAwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_navlinks_s">googlebooks</a>.
<br>
<br>
M. Reid, Decomposition of toric morphisms, in Arithmetic and Geometry, papers dedicated to I.R. Shafarevich, Birkh&auml;user 1983, Vol II, 395--418.
